{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","data":{"body":"IMPLEMENTATION FINDING (data recovery, 2026-07-15): the on-disk active+.retired scan is INSUFFICIENT for compacted tickets. Verified on dc58-af7b-034c-4a4e (an older ticket): its dir holds only {2 COMMENT, 1 EDIT, 1 REVIEW_RESULT, 1 SNAPSHOT} — CREATE + all STATUS events were folded into the SNAPSHOT with NO .retired STATUS/CREATE files on disk. So reopen_count, the post-claim-edit window, and ticket_type CANNOT be recovered from on-disk events for compacted tickets. This confirms report §5's method (git-object walk across all tickets-branch refs — 15,802 event files) is the REQUIRED primary recovery path, not a fallback (the subagent's '.retired gives full history' held in aggregate but not for old folded tickets). Recovery design: (a) SNAPSHOT.data.compiled_state (23-key reduced state) gives ticket_type/level/last_reopened_at; SNAPSHOT.data.source_event_uuids lists folded event uuids; (b) 'git -C .tickets-tracker rev-list --objects --all' + 'git cat-file' recovers the historical STATUS/EDIT/CREATE blobs (dc58: 3 STATUS/CREATE blobs recoverable), dedup by uuid, group by ticket_id from the blob path. STATUS shape confirmed {status,current_status}; EDIT changes live in data.fields (NOT data.description). WIP: docs/research/task-decomposition-sota-2026.md (recovered, uncommitted on disk) + harnesses/mine_outcome_corpus.py (v1, on-disk-scan — being reworked to git-object walk). Both tickets (E1 + epic 6982) are claimed/in_progress under RebarBotNava."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1784163874608652001,"uuid":"4ed365af-9925-4022-917d-95d1f4423abe"}